<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-519-681  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 519 681.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  Oct 11 1990 v16 n21 p2(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Plesman Publications Ltd. (Canada) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>U of T gets Royal Trust donation. (Univ of Toronto to establishBusiness Information Centre)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Royal Trust Bank Corp. (Communication systems).andO;Topic:     Toronto, University ofDonationCD-ROMData BasesInformation Storage and RetrievalLibrary NetworksBusiness EducationCanada.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UofT gets Royal Trust donationandM;TORONTO -- The Faculty of Management at the University of Toronto and RoyalTrust Corp. have concluded a deal which will bring CD-ROM database and onlineinformation retrieval technology along with thousands of current books andperiodicals to the UofT's business school library.andM;Royal Trust donated the resources of its corporate library to U of T,enabling the Faculty of Management to create a state-of-the-art BusinessInformation Centre (BIC) nand to advance towards its goal of becoming thepre-eminent business school in Canada.andM;In return for its gift to the university, Royal Trust receives access to theFaculty of Management's BIC, while no longer having to bear the ongoingoperating costs of its own corporate library.andP;  The company has guaranteed theFaculty's BIC $200,000 in annual revenue for three years, in payment forinformation retrieval services.andM;Access to the CD-ROM business databases will be free of charge to Faculty ofManagement students.andM;However, the BIC will recover its costs for on-line searches of externaldatabases and for on-line or CD-ROM printouts on user-pay basis.andO;</TEXT></DOC>